# Obsidian Vault Conventions

The rest of this file documents the conventions skills depend on. Adjust paths and patterns to match your vault layout, then keep them in sync as you evolve the system.

## Paths

Skills read these paths from this section. Edit them to match your vault. Paths are relative to `$OBSIDIAN_VAULT`.

| Key | Path | Used by |
|-----|------|---------|
| **daily_notes** | `_weekly/_daily/` | `/today`, `/connect-sync` |
| **captures** | `_inbox/captures/` | `/capture` |
| **templates** | `_templates/` | `/today`, `/capture` |
| **connections** | `_connections/` | `/connect-sync` |
| **people** | `_people/` | `/capture`, `/connect-sync` |
| **projects** | `_projects/` | `/capture`, `/connect-sync` |
| **strategy** | `_strategy/` | `/capture` |

`/obsidian-setup` seeds this table. Change a value and skills pick up the change on their next run.

## Templates

Templates live in `_templates/` and are referenced by skills via `obsidian create name="..." template="..."`.

| Situation | Template |
|-----------|----------|
| 1:1 with direct report | `1on1-template.md` |
| 1:1 with another manager | `peer-1on1.md` |
| Daily planning | `daily-note.md` |
| Standup | `standup-template.md` |

Templates use `{{date}}` as a placeholder, resolved automatically by `obsidian create`.

## Naming Conventions — Kebab-Case

All filenames use **kebab-case**: lowercase, hyphens instead of spaces, no special characters.

- 1:1 notes: `YYYY-MM-DD-1on1-firstname-lastname.md`
- Standups: `YYYY-MM-DD-team-standup.md`
- Daily notes: `YYYY-MM-DD.md` (matches Obsidian daily note plugin)
- Meeting notes: `YYYY-MM-DD-meeting-topic.md`
- `&` becomes `-and-`, colons/parentheses/brackets are removed, multiple hyphens collapse

## Folder Structure

```
_templates/        # Note templates (referenced by skills, don't modify casually)
_weekly/_daily/    # Daily planning notes (matches Obsidian daily note plugin)
_inbox/            # Captures from /capture
  captures/
_strategy/         # Strategic area pages (used as tags by /capture)
_people/           # One file per person (used for connections)
_projects/         # One file per project (used for connections)
_connections/      # Auto-maintained by /connect-sync
  themes/
  people/
  concerns/
  decisions/
```

Adjust to your taste. Most skills can be configured to use different paths — check each skill's frontmatter and code.

## Obsidian CLI

The `obsidian` CLI (install separately) is the bridge for vault interaction. Skills prefer it when available:

- `obsidian daily:read` / `obsidian daily:append` — read/write today's daily note
- `obsidian create name="..." template="..."` — create notes from templates
- `obsidian tasks todo file="..." verbose` — list incomplete tasks with line numbers
- `obsidian task file="..." line=N done` — mark a task complete
- `obsidian read file="..."` / `obsidian search:context query="..."` — read and search
- `obsidian links file="..."` / `obsidian backlinks file="..."` — navigate the graph (used by `/connect-sync deep`)

Skills work without the CLI — they fall back to direct file operations — but lose some convenience.

## Formatting

- Use `[[kebab-case-name]]` wikilinks when referencing people or notes (e.g., `[[derrick-henry]]`)
- Use `- [ ]` for action items (trackable checkboxes)
- Templates use `{{date}}` placeholder (resolved automatically by `obsidian create`)

## Action Items

Action item tracking is critical to the daily note flow. When asked about open tasks:

- Search for uncompleted checkboxes: `- [ ]`
- Look in recent daily notes and 1:1s
- Always include **yesterday's note first**, even if outside the past week
- Review the last 7 days in **reverse chronological order, starting from yesterday**
- Don't skip recent days (e.g., don't skip Monday if today is Tuesday)
- Help transfer incomplete items to new daily notes (the `/today` skill handles this)

## Carryover Annotations

The `/today` skill leaves an audit trail on every action item it touches. When you see these in old notes, that's why:

- `- [x] carried over to YYYY-MM-DD - {item text}` — moved to a future daily note
- `- [x] dropped on YYYY-MM-DD - {item text}` — explicitly dropped (usually after going stale)
- `- [x] declined to carry over on YYYY-MM-DD - {item text}` — presented but not selected

In new daily notes, items have a `(carried forward N days)` suffix so you can see how long something has been on the list.
